725528f-c.title: Queens: 63rd Avenue - 97th Street
725528f-c.text:
Sixty-third Avenue (foreground not shpwn) east of 97th Street
(about 55 ft.) showing in three views the H. Vanderveer house of
18'3. H.S. and H.G. Vanderveer were the owners in 1891 and 1909
respectively. It was erected by Henry Suydam Vanderveer in 1850
and remodeled and enlarged by him in 1873. J. Vanderveer was the
owner in 1896. In 1923 it was John Vanderveers residence. The
rear building seen in view No. 3 is 47-09 Sixty-third Drive.
April 1923
Views 1 and 2
View 3: March 1925
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection

725529f-a.title: Queens: 63rd Avenue - 97th Street
725529f-a.text:
Sixty-third Avenue, (along front of white house seen in view),
south side, east of 97th Street (left, through group of trees when
constructed) showing in two views the rear of the house and out-
buildings and farmland of H. Vanderveer who owned this property and
lived here in 1860.
April 1923
Views 1 and 2
